🗄 Technical
Topic: DBMS (Database Management System)
1️⃣ Clear Theory (Easy Language)

A DBMS (Database Management System) is software used to:

Store data

Organize data

Retrieve data efficiently

📌 Example:

Student database

Bank system

Railway reservation system

2️⃣ Basic Concepts
🔹 Database

Collection of related data.

🔹 Table

Data stored in rows & columns.

ID	Name	Age
1	Ram	20
🔹 Key Types

Primary Key → Unique identifier (No duplicate, No null)

Foreign Key → Links two tables

🔹 SQL (Structured Query Language)

Used to interact with database.

Examples:

SELECT → Retrieve data

INSERT → Add data

UPDATE → Modify data

DELETE → Remove data

3️⃣ Important DBMS Concepts
🔹 Normalization

Removes redundancy

Improves efficiency

🔹 Data Integrity

Ensures accuracy of data

🔹 DBMS vs File System
DBMS	File System
Organized	Unorganized
Secure	Less secure
No redundancy	High redundancy
🧠 Quick Tricks

Primary key = unique

Foreign key = relationship

SQL = query language

DBMS = data management

